In a large bowl, dissolve bouillon in water. Stir in egg, oats, barbecue sauce, onion, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, garlic powder, salt, pepper and chili powder. Add beef and mix well. Press into an ungreased 8-in. x 4-in. x 2-in. loaf pan. Bake at 350 degrees F for 1 hour. Top with ketchup. Bake 5-10 minutes longer or until meat thermometer reads 160 degrees F. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.